==English==
===Etymology===
LL. [[adfiliare]], [[affiliare]], to adopt as son; ad + [[filius]] son: cf. F. [[affilier]].

===Pronunciation===
'''Noun:''' 
*IPA: [[WEAE]] /ʌˈfɪl.i.et/
*{{audio|en-us-affiliate-noun.ogg|Audio (US)}}

'''Verb'''
*{{audio|en-us-affiliate-verb.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
'''affiliate'''
#Someone or something that is affiliated, or associated; a member of a group of associated things.
#:''The local channel was an '''affiliate''' of a national network.''

===Transitive Verb===
'''affiliate'''
# To adopt; to receive into a family as a son; hence, to bring or receive into close connection; to ally.
# To fix the paternity of; &mdash; said of an illegitimate child; as, to affiliate the child to (or on or upon) one man rather than another.
# To connect in the way of descent; to trace origin to.
# To attach (to) or unite (with); to receive into a society as a member, and initiate into its mysteries, plans, etc.; &mdash; followed by to or with.

